cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a framework for improving feature attribution methods in deep learning models by incorporating prior knowledge about the importance of features. The paper discusses the limitations of current attribution methods and proposes a new approach that learns a relationship between prior information and feature importance. This paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with deep learning models and their interpretation, which are relevant to these sub-categories.
